    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>These are very good &#8212; a bit too sweet for my taste, but by reducing both sugars by 1 tbsp each, they are perfect. Peanut butter and chocolate are the perfect combo&#8230;. try this: mix 1/3 c peanut butter with 3 tbsp confectioners sugar. Drop about half the chocolate dough on cookie sheet, and flatten mounds slightly. Drop approx 1 tsp of peanut butter mixture on each chocolate cookie and then top with remaining chocolate dough.Press down slighlty. Bake as directed. 100% yummy!</p>
    </div>

