    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09951176656072945150" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Rebecca</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/10/d-e-s-s-e-r-t/#comment-7040"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-11-13T21:06:00-05:00">Tuesday, November 13, 2007 at 9:06 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Have you ever used Guittard chocolate (www.eguittard.com)? It&#8217;s really superior chocolate even if it is a little hard to find. It&#8217;s fantastic for baking &#8211; very satiny and smooth, melty without totally losing its shape. It&#8217;s the only chocolate I ever use in baking &#8211; try it, the difference between Guittard chocolate and any other American brand will astound you.</p>
    </div>

