  <li id="comment-7063" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/10/d-e-s-s-e-r-t/#comment-7063"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-11-25T00:58:00-05:00">Tuesday, November 25, 2008 at 12:58 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I wanted to chime in on the question about Dutch-process cocoa. I&#8217;ve tried this recipe both ways, and I prefer the Dutch-process; the cookies tasted much richer. I can&#8217;t be sure, but I think using Dutch-process cocoa also lends the cookies a kind of liqueur flavor. Everyone is always asking me if I&#8217;ve added alcohol!</></>(Btw, this is my first time leaving a comment, but I&#8217;ve been using your recipes for a while now &#8212; always to rave reviews.)</></>Thanks,</>Karen</p>
    </div>

